Can't remember where I found this, but this function allows you to go up any level of dirs without specifying an infinite number of aliases.<p>Usage: up {x} where x is the number of directories you want to go up (e.g., 3)<p>function up()
{
  local arg=${1:-1}
  local dir=""
  while [ $arg -gt 0 ]; do
    dir="../$dir"
    arg=$(($arg - 1));
  done
  cd $dir >&/dev/null
}
